Hello,
I was using the rec feature today and tried to display my deck, everything went white. I tried it on mobile and got the same result, although I was using google chrome on both occasions.
I figured it was a card in the deck list that was causing the problem so I kept trying half and halfs of the deck to find the culprit and it was the card "Seance" which has an accented e in the card title. The name "Seance" is accepted on tapped out, and even with the card in the list I could still get recommendations, just not see my deck. Be great if you could fix this, much appreciated.

attachments.fallback: David Keatts updated the description of better supervisor logging.
attachments.text:
currently, some things are going to /var/log/edhrec through python logging, but there are no timestamps so it's not useful unless you're looking for something specific.  stdout/err are in supervisor but are too big a hassle to get to.

recently I learned that supervisor allows you to set up stdout_logfile and stderr_logfile for all processes.  right now these are all going into /tmp/, but I'd like to [1] delete my current /var/log/edhrec stuff, [2] make everything go to stdout/err (slackalerts are still fine), [3] configure logrotate, [4] tie into slack somehow, maybe just stderr, or maybe not slack but something else web-browser accessible
